HEADWORD: Drosera
<hw>Dros"e*ra</hw> <pr>(dr⟦ocr⟧s"⟦esl⟧*r⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>drosero`s</grk> dewy.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of low perennial or biennial plants, the leaves of which
are beset with gland-tipped bristles. See <er>Sundew</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

